After the recent update to 1.5.5, driver emits a warning, when the _connectTimeoutMS_ option is set. 
In our Dev/Ci/RC environments we are logging and throwing an exception on every warning/error/notice from PHP (fail first prinicple). We also use doctrine with _connectTimeoutMS_ option in connection string. 
{code:php}
error_reporting(E_ALL);
ini_set('display_errors', 1);
MongoLog::setModule(MongoLog::ALL);
MongoLog::setLevel(MongoLog::WARNING);
....
// Doctrine connection
        'connection'    => [
            'odm_default' => [
                'connectionString' => 'mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/?connectTimeoutMS=1000&socketTimeoutMS=120000'
            ],
        ],
{code}
Unfortunately the recent update to 1.5.5 driver ( specifically the fix for the ticket https://jira.mongodb.org/browse/PHP-1107 ), broke our system, because the mongo-php driver emits warning, that the option _connectTimeoutMS_ was changed and our system stops.

I would like to ask, why are you logging the setting of the _connectTimeoutMS_ option as a *warning*?(https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-php-driver/blob/master/mcon/parse.c line 570)  Is this option deprecated, or does it lead to some problems? If not, could you lower the logging level for it, because in this case it is not a *warning* but *info* or *notice*. 
If the option really should not be used, then it would be nice, if you could change the documentation or marked the option as deprecated.
